SLS 26RS-4365 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 168
BY SENATOR BARTHELEMY
HOUSING. Creates the Dream Starter Program Task Force to study the development and
implementation of a unified statewide home ownership assistance program.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To create and provide for the Dream Starter Program Task Force to study the development
3 and implementation of a unified statewide homeownership assistance program and
4 to evaluate program design, funding mechanisms, eligibility frameworks, and market
5 feasibility.
6 WHEREAS, expanding sustainable homeownership strengthens workforce stability,
7 local tax bases, and long-term household wealth, and is a critical driver of economic mobility
8 across Louisiana; and
9 WHEREAS, despite income-qualified households being otherwise mortgage-ready,
10 many Louisiana residents remain unable to purchase homes due to structural barriers,
11 including lack of generational wealth, limited access to upfront capital for down payments
12 and closing costs, and reduced exposure to homeownership pathways; and
13 WHEREAS, research and policy analysis demonstrate that disparities in
14 homeownership are not explained by income alone, but are also driven by intergenerational
15 access to wealth and opportunity, requiring targeted and data-informed policy solutions; and
16 WHEREAS, the Legislature of Louisiana has considered multiple approaches to
17 expanding access to homeownership, including the "Dream Starter Act" and the "Louisiana
18 First-Generation Homebuyer Assistance Act" which reflect shared objectives but differ in
